# SkillGrow Backend

## Quick Start
1. `cd server`
2. `cp .env.example .env` and set values
3. Ensure MongoDB is running locally
4. `npm install`
5. `npm run dev`

## Test with cURL
- Register:
```
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register \
 -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
 -d '{"name":"Sinchana","email":"s@test.com","password":"secret123"}'
```
- Login:
```
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login \
 -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
 -d '{"email":"s@test.com","password":"secret123"}'
```
- Create Log (replace TOKEN):
```
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/logs \
 -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
 -d '{"subject":"DBMS","topic":"Normalization","confidence":2,"minutes":30}'
```
- Stats:
```
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN" http://localhost:5000/api/logs/stats
```

## Notes
- Keep only MongoDB; remove any MySQL packages.
- Set `CLIENT_ORIGIN` to your Vite URL for CORS (e.g., http://localhost:5173).
- Dates are ISO strings; the API accepts an optional `date` field for backfilling.
